xmlfy
------------------------------------------
The xmlfy command is a powerful yet lightweight tool that primarily caters for
converting ASCII, UTF-8, UTF-16 or UTF-32 based output into XML format on the
fly and dealing with common issues associated with this kind of transformation.
xmlfy can be invoked from the command line or from within a shell script to
transform data quickly, easily and reliably.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2
  ruby-2.6.4-1

Canonical website:
  http://xmlfy.sf.net/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/xmlfy/xmlfy-1.5.7-src.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack xmlfy-1.5.7-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./xmlfy-1.5.7-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/xmlfy-1.5.7-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/xmlfy-1.5.7-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(xmlfy)
  /usr/bin/xmlfy.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/xmlfy.README
  /usr/share/doc/xmlfy/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/xmlfy/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/xmlfy/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/xmlfy/README
  /usr/share/man/man1/xmlfy.1.gz

